sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.eclipse.core.runtime

Class ForwardingPluginConsole

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
      • sk.stuba.fiit.perconik.eclipse.core.runtime.ForwardingPluginConsole
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.io.Flushable, java.lang.Appendable, java.lang.AutoCloseable, PluginConsole
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ActivityListener.Console, ActivityListener.Log, TimeHookConsole

    public abstract class ForwardingPluginConsole
extends com.google.common.collect.ForwardingObject
implements PluginConsole
    A plug-in console which forwards all its method calls to another plug-in console. Subclasses should override one or more methods to modify the behavior of the backing plug-in console as desired per the decorator pattern.

    Note that this class does not forward the equals and hashCode methods through to the backing object. See ForwardingObject for more details.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Pavol Zbell
